    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-04-18T04:10:42+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-18T04:10:42+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-17T18:40:42Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-17T18:40:42Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high pressure system south of the Bight extends a ridge over SA. The high will slowly move east over the weekend ahead of a cold front which will slip to the south of SA and weaken. The high will remain near stationary in the southern Tasman Sea, maintaining a ridge across the state early next week.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW010" description="West Coast" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-04-18T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-19T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-17T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-18T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Slight chance of a shower near the coast this evening. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm west of Ceduna during this afternoon and evening. Winds north to northeasterly 25 to 40 km/h shifting south to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h during the afternoon and evening. Daytime maximum temperatures 30 to 35.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">Moderate</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 10:00am to 3:10pm, UV Index predicted to reach 6 [High]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-04-19T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-20T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-18T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-19T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Slight chance of a shower in the early morning. The chance of a thunderstorm in the early morning. Sunny afternoon. Winds southeast to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h becoming light in the early morning then becoming southeast to southwesterly 20 to 30 km/h in the morning. Overnight temperatures falling to around 16 with daytime temperatures reaching the low to high 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-04-20T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-21T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-19T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-20T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Sunny. The chance of morning fog south of Streaky Bay. Winds east to southeasterly 15 to 25 km/h tending east to northeasterly during the day. Overnight temperatures falling to between 10 and 13 with daytime temperatures reaching 25 to 32.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-04-21T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-22T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-20T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-21T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Slight chance of a shower west of Nullarbor in the afternoon and evening. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm west of Nullarbor in the afternoon and evening. Winds northeasterly 20 to 30 km/h tending northwest to northeasterly 25 to 40 km/h during the morning then tending southeast to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 12 and 20 with daytime temperatures reaching the low to mid 30s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
